Sunhawk flew in larger and larger circles.  The ground appeared rocky 
and he doubted they had explosives to clear land (noone can tell me a 
landscape I make one up).  He finally spotted a big enough clearing 
and set down about 6 miles from the base to the North East.  He 
opened his commlink.

Sunhawk:  I think I have something.  This place is perfect for a 
sensor.  Should I stay here to help when you bring the equipment or 
come back and get it myself.
